  "text": "Three Japanese foods. Most people skip all of them. Edamame, eight grams of fiber, one cup. That's it. Done. Natto, fermented soybeans, five grams per serving. Also probiotics. Also protein. Overachiever. Burdock root, six grams per half cup. You've never ordered it. You should. Meanwhile, you're eating sashimi. Great protein, zero fiber. That's fine. That's a trade-off. But if you want the fiber, these three, that's the whole list. Recipes at daily-life-hacks.com.",
